revision.text:
The '''Abrincatui''' were a [[Gaul|Gallic]] tribe ([[Pliny the Elder|Plin.]] iv. 18), not mentioned by [[Julius Caesar]], whose frontier was near the [[Curiosolites]]. Their town [[Ingena (Gaul)|Ingena]], called ''Abrincatae'' in the [[Notitia dignitatum]], has given its name to the modern [[Avranches]]; and their territory would probably correspond to the division of [[Avranchin]]. The Abrincatui became a client tribe of the Venelli until the Roman occupation in BC 49, when they were separated.<ref name="Mountain1998">{{citation|author=Harry Mountain|title=The Celtic Encyclopedia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LTbc1GIAwcIC&pg=PA115|year=1998|publisher=Universal-Publishers|isbn=978-1-58112-890-1|pages=115–}}</ref>

