{{Infobox diocese | jurisdiction = Apostolic Administration<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese --> | name = Southern Albania | latin = Administratio Apostolica Albaniae Meridionalis | local = Administratura Apostolike e Shqiperisë së Jugut | image = | image_size = frameless | image_alt = | caption = <!---- Locations ----> | country = [[Albania]] | metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Tiranë–Durrës|Tiranë–Durrës]] | territory = Southern Albania | province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Tiranë–Durrës|Tiranë–Durrës]] | coordinates = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> <!---- Statistics ----> | area_km2 = 16,172<!-- Area in square kilometers, automatically converted --> | population = 2,140,000 | population_as_of = 2014 | catholics = 3,596 | catholics_percent = 0.2 | parishes = 11<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese --> | churches = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese --> | congregations = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese --> | schools = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese --> | members = <!-- Number of members in the diocese --> <!---- Information ----> | sui_iuris_church = [[Albanian Greek Catholic Church]]{{citation needed|date=August 2018}} | rite = [[Latin Rite]] and [[Byzantine Rite]] | established = November 11, 1939 | cathedral = Pro-Cathedral of St. Mary and St. Louis in [[Vlorë]] | cocathedral = | patron = | priests = 8<!-- Number of priests in the diocese --> <!---- Current leadership ----> | pope = {{Incumbent pope}} | bishop = [[Giovanni Peragine]] | bishop_title = [[Apostolic Administrator]] | metro_archbishop = [[George Anthony Frendo]] Archbishop of Tiranë–Durrës | coadjutor = | auxiliary_bishops = | vicar_general = | emeritus_bishops = <!---- Map ----> | map = | map_alt = | map_caption = <!---- Website ----> | website = <!-- [http://example.com example.com] --> | footnotes = }}
The '''Apostolic Administration of Southern Albania''' ({{lang-sq|Administratura Apostolike e Shqiperisë së Jugut}}, {{lang-la|Administratio Apostolica Albaniae Meridionalis}}, [[Italian language|Italian]]: ''Albania Meridionale'') is an [[apostolic administration]] of the [[Catholic Church]] in [[Albania]], covering the southern regions of the country. It has jurisdiction over all Catholics on its territory, both of [[Latin Rite|Latin]] and [[Byzantine Rite|Byzantine]] rites.<ref>[http://www.vatican.va/archive/aas/documents/AAS-32-1940-ocr.pdf Acta Apostolicae Sedis, 32 (1940)], p. 139-140.</ref> It is [[suffragan]] to the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Tiranë–Durrës]].<ref>[http://www.vatican.va/archive/aas/documents/2005/febbraio%202005.pdf Acta Apostolicae Sedis, 97 (2005)], p. 131-132.</ref> Its see is [[Pro-Cathedral]] of St. Mary and St. Louis ({{lang-sq|Kisha e Shën Maria dhe Shën Luigji}}) in [[Vlorë]].
It is claimed that Apostolic Administration of Southern Albania constitutes the only component of the particular (''sui juris'') [[Albanian Greek Catholic Church]].{{citation needed|date=August 2018}} Such claims have been questioned by some leading Eastern Catholic experts.{{sfn|Galadza|2007|pp=293}}
== History == [[File:Lagekarte Apostolische Administratur Südalbanien.png|thumb|200px|right|Territory of the Apostolic Administration of Southern Albania]] On November 11, 1939, the Holy See issued the [[papal bull]] ''Inter regiones'', establishing the ''Apostolic Administration of Southern Albania''. Initially, it was created as a regular [[apostolic administration]], for all Catholics in southern regions of Albania, both of [[Latin Church|Latin]] and [[Byzantine Rite|Byzantine]] rites. Its territory was detached from the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Durrës]], and initially covered districts of Elbassan, Korca, Berat, Valona and Argyrocastro.<ref>[http://www.vatican.va/archive/aas/documents/AAS-32-1940-ocr.pdf Acta Apostolicae Sedis, 32 (1940)], p. 139-140.</ref>
Since January 25, 2005, it is suffragan to the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Tiranë-Durrës]], within the newly created metropolitan province.<ref>[http://www.vatican.va/archive/aas/documents/2005/febbraio%202005.pdf Acta Apostolicae Sedis, 97 (2005)], p. 131-132.</ref>
