The '''Apostolic Nunciature to Switzerland''' is an ecclesiastical office of the [[Catholic Church]] in [[Switzerland]].<ref name=CathHierNuncioSwitz>{{Cite web|last=Cheney |first=David M.|authorlink=|title=Nunciature to Switzerland|publisher=''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dxxch.html |accessdate=June 16, 2018}}  [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref><ref name=GCathNuncioSwitz>{{Cite web|last=Chow |first=Gabriel|authorlink=|title=Apostolic Nunciature Switzerland |publisher=''[[GCatholic.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/nunciature/nunc164.htm |accessdate=June 16, 2018}}  [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref> It is a [[foreign relations of the Holy See|diplomatic post of the Holy See]], whose representative is called the [[Apostolic Nuncio]], with the rank of an [[ambassador]]. The nunciature is located in the capital of [[Bern]].

