{{Infobox prepared food | name = Cholermus | image = | caption = | alternate_name = Swiss Pancake | country = [[Switzerland]] | region = | creator = | course = [[Supper]] [[Breakfast]] | type = [[Pancake]] | served = | main_ingredient = | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Cholermues''' or '''Cholermus''' is a traditional dish from the [[Obwalden|Canton of Obwalden]] in [[Central Switzerland]]. It is a kind of [[pancake]],<ref name="food links">{{cite web|title=Swiss Food Glossary and Food Terms|url=http://www.food-links.com/countries/switzerland/food-glossary-switzerland.php|publisher=Food-links.com|accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> or "shredded, fried crepe",<ref>{{cite web|last=Anton Frederick Uhlea & Louis Evan Grivettib|first=|title=Alpine and Brazilian Swiss food patterns after a century of isolation|url=https://scholar.google.com.au/scholar?q=Cholermus&hl=en&btnG=Search&as_sdt=1%2C5&as_sdtp=on|accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> that is typically eaten for supper.
This preparation should not be confused with Hollermus or Holdermus, which is an [[Sambucus|elderberry]] mash.
