{{Infobox book | name = The Man Who Spoke Snakish | title_orig = Mees, kes teadis ussisõnu | translator = | image = Mees, kes teadis ussisõnu.jpg | image_size = 150px | caption = | author = Andrus Kivirähk | illustrator = Andres Rõhu | cover_artist = | country = {{flag|Estonia}} | language = [[Estonian language|Estonian]] | series = | subject = | genre = | published = 2007 (Eesti Keele Sihtasutus) | media_type = Print, Audio | pages = 381 | isbn = 978-9985-79-178-3 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} ''''' The Man Who Spoke Snakish ''''' (Estonian: ''Mees, kes teadis ussisõnu'') is a novel by [[Estonia]]n author [[Andrus Kivirähk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estlit.ee/?id=11669&author=10876&tpl=1063&c_tpl=1071|title=Estonian Literature}}</ref> It was first published in 2007. In 2008 an audiobook was published, read by the Estonian actor [[Tiit Sukk]].<ref>http://ester.nlib.ee/search/i?SEARCH=9789985317938{{dead link|date=May 2016}}</ref> It has been translated into English (2015), as well as Czech (2011), Latvian (2011), French (as ''L'Homme qui savait la langue des serpents'', 2013), Russian (2014), Danish (2015), Dutch (2015), Hungarian (2015), Spanish (2017) and German (2017).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estlit.ee/elis/?cmd=book&id=86312|title=''Mees, kes teadis ussisõnu'' at the Estonian Literature Center}}</ref> In 2009 a board game with the same name was released by the game developer [[Revaler]] in cooperation with the newspaper ''[[Eesti Päevaleht]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/55828/mees-kes-teadis-ussisonu|title=Mees, kes teadis ussisõnu (2009)|work=BoardGameGeek}}</ref> It is set in an imaginary Estonia during the Middle Ages.
The French translation was awarded the [[Grand Prix de l'Imaginaire]] for the best foreign-language novel in 2014.
The protagonist is Leemet, an Estonian who is part of a diminishing group of forest-dwellers, upholding ancient traditions and speaking the ancient "snake-tongue" which lets them control animals and speak with snakes.
