{{Politics of Burundi}}

The '''Movement for the Rehabilitation of Citizens–Rurenzangemero''' ({{lang-fr|Mouvement pour la Réhabilitation du Citoyen–Rurenzangemero}}, MRC–Rurenzangemero) is a [[political party]] in [[Burundi]]. It is currently led by Epitace Banyaganakandi.

==History==
The party was established in 2002, drawing most of its support from the ethnic [[Tutsi]] minority. It received 2% of the vote in the [[Burundian legislative election, 2005|2005 parliamentary elections]], winning two seats.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/bi.html#2005_National_Assembly_Election Elections in Burundi] African Elections DAtabase</ref> It subsequently joined the government, taking the Social Security and Public Service ministerial portfolios.<ref name=TL>Tom Lansford (2014) ''Political Handbook of the World 2014 '', CQ Press, p212</ref>

The party boycotted the [[Burundian legislative election, 2010|2010 parliamentary elections]] but participated in the [[Burundian legislative election, 2015|2015 Burundian parliamentary election]].<ref name=TL/>

