'''Radio Mirraya''' 101 FM, is a radio station  based in [[Juba]] owned by [[United Nations Mission in South Sudan|United Nations mission in South Sudan]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=Arab Approaches to Conflict Resolution: Mediation, Negotiation and ...|last=Frederic S Pearson|first=Nahla Yassine-Hamdan &|publisher=Routledge|year=2014|isbn=978-0-415-81744-8|location=New york|pages=296}}</ref> It began broadcasting in [[South Sudan]] on June 30, 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hirondelle.org/en/south-sudan|title=Radio Mirraya- South Sudan|last=|first=|date=|website=Horondelle.org|access-date=21 Feb 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radioline.co/listen-to-radio-miraya|title=Radio Mirraya|last=|first=|date=|website=Online Radio|access-date=21 Feb 2018}}</ref>

It provides news and information 24 hours, 7 days a week in English and Arabic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://audioboom.com/channel/radiomiraya|title=Radio Mirraya|last=|first=|date=|website=Audioboom.com|access-date=21 Feb 2018}}</ref> It is the fifth [[United Nations Radio|UN radio station]] operating on behalf of UN peace operation in 2006.<ref>{{Cite book|title=United Nations Peace Operations|last=|first=|publisher=United Nations. Dept. of Public Information|year=2006|isbn=|location=United nations|pages=32}}</ref>

